Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the deployment of heterogeneous networks and the coordination of base-station transmissions to minimize interference. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the physical layer aspects of time-domain ICIC in Rel-10. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the back-hauling aspects of time-domain ICIC in Rel-10, which is related to multimedia transmission. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the network layer aspects of time-domain ICIC in Rel-10, which involves system-level coordination. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on hardware design or implementation.
